[div class=p 
	[em 
		"Square's Tom Sawyer
	]em
	" (スクウェアのトム・ソーヤ) is a role-playing game for the Famicom that was released only in Japan. It was developed by Square and is a loose video game adaptation of the book 
	[em 
		"The Adventures of Tom Sawyer
	]em
	". The game is notorious in the west for its depiction of African-Americans through antiquated blackface caricatures, the most prominent example being the character Jim. As for the gameplay, it is similar to 
	[em 
		"Final Fantasy II
	]em
	" in that there is no experience system; items are used to boost your stats. The combat also goes from traditional turn-based attacking to games of rock-paper-scissors halfway through the game.
	$LF
]div
